author: @FreedomForKashmir
text: STOP and read this.... it will help you. Whole video is very good and educative  but there is a problem with hypercorn command(hypercorn main:app --reload) at the end. When running it on localhost of your laptop ... its fine. But when running it on cloud you would have to explicitly give it host and post number .... otherwise you won't be able to access it using DNS or public IP of your EC2 instance Use this command on cloud terminal >>>>> hypercorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 OR(if you are using uvicorn) Use this command >>>>> uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000    hope it would help
